# VLAN & VTP Lab (Multi-Switch with DHCP)

## Objective
Configure VLANs across multiple switches using VTP.  
Ensure VLANs are synchronized between switches.  
Configure DHCP on the router so all hosts receive IP addresses and can communicate.

## Requirements
- 3 × Cisco L2 IOU Switches  
- 1 × Cisco L3 IOU Router  
- 10 × VPC  

## What You Will Do
- Configure VTP domain and modes (server, client, transparent)  
- Create VLANs on the VTP server switch  
- Ensure VLANs propagate to other switches  
- Configure trunk links between switches  
- Assign correct VLANs to access ports  
- Configure DHCP on router  
- Verify IP assignment and connectivity  

## Expected Outcome
- VLANs are synchronized across switches  
- All VPCs receive correct IP addresses via DHCP  
- Hosts across VLANs can communicate as expected  

## Lab Files
- IOU images are available in the Google Drive link  
- Follow setup steps to import into PNETLab  
- Import the `.unl` file to access the lab  

## Objectives (Detailed)
Refer to the objective diagram inside the `.unl` file:  
